{"lemma":"عُورِ","slug":"عُورِ","root":"ع.#.ر","root_slug":"ع-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30974","","n30979","n30980"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become one-eyed or blind in one eye"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/iʕ.war.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30974","headword_ar":"عَوِرَ","root":"Ewr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) said of a man, (O,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEowaru","text_ar":"يَعْوَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawarN","text_ar":"عَوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, blind of one eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became one-eyed; wanting one eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of his eyes sank in its socket:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of his eyes dried up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see what next follows:] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra","text_ar":"عَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEaAru","text_ar":"يَعَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEwr~","text_ar":"اعورّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEwAr~","text_ar":"اعوارّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sgh, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawirato Eayonuhu","text_ar":"عَوِرَتْ عَيْنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S, IKtt, O, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEowaru","text_ar":"تَعْوَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawarN","text_ar":"عَوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IKtt, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArato","text_ar":"عَارَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaAru","text_ar":"تَعَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, IKtt, O) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiEaAru","text_ar":"تِعَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IKtt, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEwr~t","text_ar":"اعورّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Az, S, IKtt, O;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEwAr~t","text_ar":"اعوارّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Az, O, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eye became blind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became wanting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sank in its socket:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA.) Ibn-Ahmar says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aEaArato Eayonuhu A^amo lamo taEaAraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Has his eye become blind or has it not indeed become blind?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaArano","text_ar":"تَعَارَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but, pausing, he makes it to end with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":": in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawirato","text_ar":"عَوِرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is preserved unaltered because it is so preserved in the original form, which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEowar~ato","text_ar":"اِعْوَرَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", on account of the quiescence of the letter immediately preceding: then the augmentatives, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the teshdeed, are suppressed, and thus the verb becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawira","text_ar":"عَوِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": for that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEwr~t","text_ar":"اعورّت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the original form is shown by the form of the sister-verbs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisowad~a","text_ar":"اِسْوَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHomar~a","text_ar":"اِحْمَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the analogy of verbs significant of faults and the like,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEoraj~a","text_ar":"اِعْرَجَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEomaY~a","text_ar":"اِعْمَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the original forms of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earija","text_ar":"عَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiYa","text_ar":"عَمِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; though these may not have been heard. (S, O. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayida","text_ar":"صَيِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArati Alr~akiy~apu","text_ar":"عَارَتِ الرَّكِيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEuwru","text_ar":"تَعُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEowaru","text_ar":"تَعْوَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaAru","text_ar":"تَعَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"?], (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The well became filled up."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArahu","text_ar":"عَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEuwruhu","text_ar":"يَعُورُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEuwarahu","text_ar":"اَعُوَرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEowaArN","text_ar":"اـِعْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ew~rhu","text_ar":"عوّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEowiyrN","text_ar":"تَعْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rendered him blind of one eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra Eayonahu","text_ar":"عَارَ عَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, IKtt, O, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEuwruhaA","text_ar":"يَعُورُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaworN","text_ar":"عَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IKtt;) and (more commonly, M) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowarahaA","text_ar":"اَعْوَرَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ew~rhA","text_ar":"عوّرها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, IKtt, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put out his eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, Msb: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to sink in its socket."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) Some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eurotu Eayonahu","text_ar":"عُرْتُ عَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaArahaA","text_ar":"اَعَارَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[sic] are from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAy^irN","text_ar":"عَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra","text_ar":"عَارَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~akiy~apa","text_ar":"الرَّكِيَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEArhA","text_ar":"اعارها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same as ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ew~rhA","text_ar":"عوّرها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He marred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoiled, the well, so that the water dried up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he filled it up with earth, so that the springs thereof became stopped up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euyuwna AlmyaAhi","text_ar":"عُيُونَ الميَاهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ew~r","text_ar":"عوّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he stopped up the sources of the waters:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayona Alr~akiy~api","text_ar":"عَيْنَ الرَّكِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ew~r","text_ar":"عوّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he filled up the source of the well, so that the water dried up."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArahu","text_ar":"عَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEuwruhu","text_ar":"يَعُورُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEiyruhu","text_ar":"يَعِيرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or the aor. is not used, or, accord. to IJ, it is scarcely ever used, (TA,) or some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuEuwruhu","text_ar":"يُعُورُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yaakoob,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEiyruhu","text_ar":"يَعِيرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Aboo-Shibl,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, took, and went away with, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^adoriY A^aY~u","text_ar":"مَا اَدْرِى اَىُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaraAdi EaArahu","text_ar":"الجَرَادِ عَارَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I know not what man went away with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said to be only used in negative phrases: but Lh mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAka Eurotahu","text_ar":"اَرَاكَ عُرْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eirotahu","text_ar":"عِرْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I see thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hold thee, to have gone away with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":":] IJ says, It seems that they have scarcely ever used the aor. of this verb because it occurs in a prov. respecting a thing that has passed away. (TA.)       -A4-  See also 3 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er","text_ar":"عر"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["O","K","S","Az","IKtt","Msb","TA","M","A","Sh"]},{"entry_id":"n30979","headword_ar":"عَوَرٌ","root":"Ewr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawira","text_ar":"عَوِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, O, K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawarapN","text_ar":"عَوَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness, faultiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsoundness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaworapN","text_ar":"عَوْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"badness, foulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unseemliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a thing:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disgrace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disfigurement."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaArN","text_ar":"عَوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^amoru bayonanaA EawarN","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَمْرُ بَيْنَنَا عَوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair, that we do by turns."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaHN","text_ar":"رَوَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30980","headword_ar":"عَوِرٌ","root":"Ewr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no keeper"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guardian;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a gap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an opening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a breach,"},{"kind":"text","text":"exposing it to thieves and the like;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEowirN","text_ar":"مُعْوِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnN muEowirN","text_ar":"مَكَانٌ مُعْوِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place in which one fears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place in which"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in one of my copies of the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu","text_ar":"مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one fears being cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pierced"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 4)]; (S, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnN EaworapN","text_ar":"مَكَانٌ عَوْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is doubly tropical: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN muEowirapN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ مُعْوِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road in which is an opening, in which one fears losing his way and being cut off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEowirN","text_ar":"مُعْوِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within the power of a person; open, and exposed: appearing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reach:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a place"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feared."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) I'Ab and some others read, in the Kur [xxxiii. 13],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a buyuwtanaA EawirapN","text_ar":"اـِنَّ بُيُوتَنَا عَوِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu EaworapK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ عَوْرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) i. e., (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily our houses are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"open and exposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not protected, but, on the contrary, within the power of thieves, having no men in them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) or it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEowirapN","text_ar":"مُعْوِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next to the enemy, so that our goods will be stolen from them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaworapN","text_ar":"عَوْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one."}],"source_refs":["TA","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}